      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Here are the results for the paper **arXiv 2603.20396**:\n\n**\"Compression is all you need: Modeling Mathematics\"**\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The paper (arXiv:2603.20396v1 [cs.AI], submitted 20 Mar 2026) is authored by **Vitaly Aksenov** (Logical Intelligence), **Eve Bodnia** (Logical Intelligence), **Michael H. Freedman** (Logical Intelligence; Center of Mathematical Sciences and Applications, Harvard University), and **Michael Mulligan** (Logical Intelligence; Department of Physics and Astronomy, University of California, Riverside)."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n### Summary of the Paper\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The paper examines how human mathematics (HM) — the mathematics humans discover and value — is a vanishingly small subset of formal mathematics (FM), the totality of all valid deductions."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The authors argue that HM is distinguished by its compressibility through hierarchically nested definitions, lemmas, and theorems."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n**Key contributions:**\n\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "They model this with monoids, where a mathematical deduction is a string of primitive symbols and a definition or theorem is a named substring or macro whose use compresses the string."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "In the free abelian monoid $A_n$, a logarithmically sparse macro set achieves exponential expansion of expressivity."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "In the free non-abelian monoid $F_n$, even a polynomially-dense macro set only yields linear expansion; superlinear expansion requires near-maximal density."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "They test these models against MathLib, a large Lean 4 library of mathematics that they take as a proxy for HM."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The paper is published in the cs.AI and math.LO categories on arXiv."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\nYou can read the full paper at: [https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.20396](https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.20396)"
      }
    ],
